    "description": "The Neopostage Postal Security Device (PSD) Module functions as a software-based PSD that utilizes hardware-based cryptographic modules for securely managing and dispensing money and indicia via encryption and digital signature techniques. The module is ideally suited to Internet and high-volume mailing based applications requiring high-speed cryptographic functions. The module is designed to meet the applicable United States Postal Service Information-Based Indicium Program (USPS IBIP) specifications for postage meters.",
